main event: A civilian spotted a single unidentified object over Kettering, Ohio on March 30, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for 10 minutes, moving in a zig-zag pattern from south to north.
The object appeared as a transparent balloon with a bright star.
The sighting was reported to the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book.
Project Blue Book requested the witness complete a detailed questionnaire to provide more information about the observation.
Project Blue Book concluded the object was likely a satellite (Pegasus II).
sighted object: a transparent balloon-like object with a bright star
